video.title: Alexa & Katie
video.synopsis: Alexa is battling cancer. But with her best friend, Katie, by her side, she's also starting high school -- and ready for whatever comes next.

episodes.synopsis: Alexa's plan to hide her cancer from her classmates and start high school like everyone else is totally doable ... until she starts losing her hair.
episodes.title: Bad Hair Day

episodes.synopsis: The girls come up with a colorful solution to keep Alexa's diagnosis under wraps. But Dave's having trouble adjusting to his daughter's new look.
episodes.title: Wigs

episodes.synopsis: There's a rumor going around school that someone in the class has cancer. Katie tries out for the basketball team, and Lori starts working from home.
episodes.title: Basketball

episodes.synopsis: Alexa goes out of her way to prove she can't be punished. Jennifer surprises Jack with a backyard campout but has a hard time getting him to unplug.
episodes.title: Ungroundable

episodes.synopsis: After landing the lead in the school play, Katie's left wondering whether she actually earned it. Jennifer asks Lucas to baby-sit.
episodes.title: The Play, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Now that Alexa's secret is out, everyone's being unbearably nice -- even Gwenny. Jennifer and Jack invite themselves over to watch the World Series.
episodes.title: Picture Day

episodes.synopsis: To kiss or not to kiss? Katie's new life as a thespian has Alexa feeling a little left out. Jennifer accuses Lori of stealing her thunder.
episodes.title: The Play, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Alexa's got such a great support system at the hospital that Katie isn't sure where she stands. Lori pours her anxieties into baking.
episodes.title: Support Group

episodes.synopsis: The doctors order Alexa to stay home, but she can still come to school -- on an iPad. Jennifer works overtime to convince Jack her job is cool.
episodes.title: Winter Luau

episodes.synopsis: Alexa insists on cooking Thanksgiving dinner, but Lori has trouble letting go. Katie's desperate to connect with her dad on a deeper level.
episodes.title: Thanksgiving

episodes.synopsis: Dave can't wait to show Lucas his alma mater. And with her family away for the weekend, Alexa's ready to break all the rules.
episodes.title: Secret Sleepover

episodes.synopsis: Lucas longs for "bro time" now that Dylan and Alexa are hanging out. Dave's nose detects a cat ... and he's not wrong.
episodes.title: Winter Formal, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Alexa's first high school dance is right around the corner. But a risky flu outbreak means she might not be able to go.
episodes.title: Winter Formal, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Sophomore year's off to a great start until Katie twists her ankle, giving Alexa something else to focus on while she's waiting to hear from her doctor.
episodes.title: Second First Day

episodes.synopsis: Katie's thrilled when she's chosen to study acting abroad in London -- but the $2,000 tuition is out of her price range. Time to start doing odd jobs!
episodes.title: ChoreCats

episodes.synopsis: Katie applies for a job at the coffee shop without telling her mom. When Lucas and Gwenny go out on a date, the girls are determined to sabotage it.
episodes.title: #GWENCAS

episodes.synopsis: After getting the OK to play basketball, Alexa struggles on the court. But a heart-to-heart with a young cancer patient reminds her how far she's come.
episodes.title: Tryouts and Latte Doubts

episodes.synopsis: When Alexa and Dylan get into a fight right before the big Halloween party, Katie's sure she can fix it. But what if they're not meant to be together?
episodes.title: PB Without J

episodes.synopsis: Alexa claims she's fine -- so the girls take her shopping for a Sweet 16 dress. Back at the house, a stressed-out Lucas goes to Dave for dating advice.
episodes.title: Shop 'Til You Cry

episodes.synopsis: When Katie needs help prepping for a math midterm, Alexa offers to ask Dylan. Meanwhile, Jennifer still doesn't know her daughter has a job.
episodes.title: Katie's Beautiful Mind

episodes.synopsis: Alexa's working overtime to keep Christmas on track. But finding her old hospital bag stirs up memories that throw her off her holiday game.
episodes.title: The Ghost of Cancer Past

episodes.synopsis: It's New Year's Eve, and a bold new Katie is finally ready to confess her feelings for Ryan. Cue the fireworks -- and a flaming espresso machine!
episodes.title: New Year's ... Whoops

episodes.synopsis: An expensive mistake means Katie can't afford to go to London. But she's keeping it a secret so she doesn't ruin Alexa's epic birthday party.
episodes.title: Sweet Sixteen

episodes.synopsis: A big fight on the first day of school leaves the girls feeling way out of sync. Lucas starts college, and Lori and Dave toast their 20th anniversary.
episodes.title: 1st Day of Junior Year

episodes.synopsis: Alexa's ready to leave cancer behind her, but it's not that simple. Meanwhile, Katie's trying to balance all the things -- and it's super complicated.
episodes.title: Stupid Binder

episodes.synopsis: Being there for Spencer brings back memories Alexa would rather forget. Katie looks for leadership opportunities, and Jennifer preps for a date.
episodes.title: Always Something There to Remind Me

episodes.synopsis: Katie and Ryan don't feel the same way about each other anymore, but neither has the heart to say it. Alexa's determined to pass her driver's test.
episodes.title: Unconsciously Coupling

episodes.synopsis: Alexa's excited to see Dylan again but senses Spencer needs her more. Katie organizes a food drive, and Dave goes overboard on holiday decorating.
episodes.title: All I Want for Christmas Is You

episodes.synopsis: Katie aims high to win a community theater competition, putting unnecessary pressure on her friends -- and herself. Lucas reexamines his future.
episodes.title: Writer-Director-Nervous Wreck

episodes.synopsis: Alexa struggles to keep her "real" life -- and her life with Spencer -- separate. A horrified Katie's convinced that her mom is dating Gwenny's dad.
episodes.title: It's Just ... Weird

episodes.synopsis: Alexa takes Katie miniature golfing to get her mind off the SATs. Lori plays matchmaker when Jennifer hires a handsome handyman.
episodes.title: Panic! At the Putt Putt

episodes.synopsis: Alexa eases Katie's anxiety with an epic plan to crush senior year. Jennifer starts her new job, and Jack and Lucas help solve each other's problems.
episodes.title: Last First Day

episodes.synopsis: Alexa's full of advice after getting her driver's license — but she doesn't know everything. Meanwhile at Wired, the new hire is Katie's worst nightmare.
episodes.title: Rules for Better Barista-ing

episodes.synopsis: After dating Joe for six months, Jennifer's ready for him to meet her family and friends. It's just dinner ... but Katie's got some concerns.
episodes.title: The Girl Who Cried Yelp

episodes.synopsis: With college applications looming, an aptitude test reveals Katie's true passion. But pursuing it is scary — and Alexa's "dream job" doesn't feel right.
episodes.title: Choose Your Own Adventure

episodes.synopsis: Alexa agrees to speak at Lori's carnival-themed Stand Up to Cancer fundraiser, where Katie's coffee kiosk brews unexpected jealousy.
episodes.title: Speaking of Cancer

episodes.synopsis: College acceptance letters are here. But did Alexa and Katie get into the same school? And why are things suddenly so weird between Alexa and Spencer?
episodes.title: The Smoke Show

episodes.synopsis: Senior prom is on Saturday, and Katie needs a date. (See also: the courage to tell Alexa something important.) Lori and Joe go overboard at game night.
episodes.title: Last Dance

episodes.synopsis: The girls are finally graduating from high school and getting ready to leave home for college. But will they stay together or go their separate ways?
episodes.title: This Feels Right
